The paper deals with optimization of Markov Decision Processes (MDP) which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on optimizing specific quantiles of the cumulative reward makes it relevant to the sub-category of stochastic control (cs.SY). The use of algorithms for solving the QMDP problem makes it relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents analytical results which makes it relevant to the sub-category of mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
